ask: cmm format(printf) attribute + fix non-literal format sink (audit B7 / P0.3)

AUDIT-cmm P0.3 — Two format-string sinks via cmm_print:

  cmm.c:201           cmm_print(DEBUG_STDOUT, cmm_help);
  forward_engine.c:1598   cmm_print(DEBUG_STDOUT, output_buf);

The cmm.c:201 site is already corrected by the mono-defensive-rewrite
patch (it now reads `cmm_print(DEBUG_STDOUT, "%s", cmm_help);`), but
forward_engine.c:1598 remains. `output_buf` is a stack `char[256]`
populated by snprintf(...) from values that include conntrack data
(sa_handle / port numbers). The current secondary formats are %x/%d
of ints, but the cmm_print macro forwards its second argument
verbatim into vfprintf via cmm_print_func — so if any future change
admits a `%` byte into output_buf (e.g. log of a user-supplied label),
the result is a classic format-string vulnerability (OOB read with
%s, OOB write with %n).

Two coordinated changes (both required — applying only the attribute
breaks the build, applying only the call-site fix doesn't surface
future regressions):

1. cmm/src/cmm.h:
     void cmm_print_func(int level, const char *format, ...);
   ->
     void cmm_print_func(int level, const char *format, ...)
        __attribute__((format(printf, 2, 3)));

   This makes the compiler enforce -Wformat / -Wformat-security on
   every cmm_print() call site (the macro at cmm.h:108 expands to a
   direct cmm_print_func() call, so the attribute propagates via the
   call site automatically). With this attribute in place,
   `cmm_print(DEBUG_STDOUT, output_buf)` becomes a -Wformat-security
   diagnostic and any future `%`-bearing regression is caught at
   compile time.

2. cmm/src/forward_engine.c:1598:
     cmm_print(DEBUG_STDOUT,output_buf);
   ->
     cmm_print(DEBUG_STDOUT, "%s\n", output_buf);

   Mirrors the existing correct site at forward_engine.c:1502 where
   the same output_buf is printed via the literal-format pattern.

Userspace-only — no kernel-side delta, no ABI/UAPI change. This is
the head of the B7 D14 format-string sweep; libcli P0.1
(format(printf) attributes on every public variadic prototype in
libcli.h) is deferred to B7b — libcli has its own build path that
isn't yet wired into the audit-patch CI loop.

